SIMPLE: indefatigable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indefatigable
<hw>In`de*fat"i*ga*ble</hw>
<pr>(⟦icr⟧n`d⟦esl⟧*f⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*g⟦adot⟧*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>indefatigabilis</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>indefatigable</ets>.
See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Defatigable</er>, and cf.
<er>Infatigable</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being fatigued; not
readily exhausted; unremitting in labor or effort; untiring; unwearying;
not yielding to fatigue; <as>as, <ex>indefatigable</ex> exertions,
perseverance, application</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A constant,
<xex>indefatigable</xex> attendance.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Upborne with <qex>indefatigable</qex> wings.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unwearied; untiring; persevering;
persistent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indefatigableness</ent>⟦br⟧
